<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>Cost Analyst Case Studies — Conversation Class</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tabler/icons-webfont@2.47.0/tabler-icons.min.css" />
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --bg: #ffffff;
    --bg2: #f6f5f1;
    --bg3: #eeecea;
    --text: #1a1a18;
    --text2: #5f5e5a;
    --text3: #888780;
    --border: rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    --border2: rgba(0,0,0,0.22);
    --radius: 10px;
    --radius-sm: 6px;
    --info-bg: #e6f1fb;
    --info-text: #0c447c;
    --info-border: #185fa5;
    --success-bg: #eaf3de;
    --success-text: #27500a;
    --warn-bg: #faeeda;
    --warn-text: #633806;
    --danger-bg: #fcebeb;
    --danger-text: #791f1f;
    --purple-bg: #eeedfe;
    --purple-text: #3c3489;
    --teal-bg: #e1f5ee;
    --teal-text: #085041;
    --rose-bg: #fbe7ef;
    --rose-text: #7d1f49;
  }

  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    :root {
      --bg: #1e1e1c;
      --bg2: #2a2a28;
      --bg3: #333330;
      --text: #f0ede8;
      --text2: #b4b2a9;
      --text3: #888780;
      --border: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
      --border2: rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
      --info-bg: #042c53;
      --info-text: #b5d4f4;
      --info-border: #378add;
      --success-bg: #173404;
      --success-text: #c0dd97;
      --warn-bg: #412402;
      --warn-text: #fac775;
      --danger-bg: #501313;
      --danger-text: #f7c1c1;
      --purple-bg: #26215c;
      --purple-text: #cecbf6;
      --teal-bg: #04342c;
      --teal-text: #9fe1cb;
      --rose-bg: #4a1530;
      --rose-text: #f4b8d4;
    }
  }

  body {
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg2);
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding: 1.5rem 1rem 4rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .page-wrap { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }

  header { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  header h1 { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  header p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text2); }

  .case {
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .case-header {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .case-num {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .case-3 .case-num { background: var(--purple-bg); color: var(--purple-text); }
  .case-4 .case-num { background: var(--teal-bg); color: var(--teal-text); }
  .case-5 .case-num { background: var(--info-bg); color: var(--info-text); }
  .case-6 .case-num { background: var(--warn-bg); color: var(--warn-text); }
  .case-7 .case-num { background: var(--danger-bg); color: var(--danger-text); }
  .case-8 .case-num { background: var(--rose-bg); color: var(--rose-text); }

  .case-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text); }
  .case-subtitle { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text3); margin-top: 1px; }

  .case-body { padding: 1.25rem; }

  .scenario-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text3);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .scenario-text {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text2);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--border2);
  }

  .vocab-chips {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .chip {
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border2);
    color: var(--text2);
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text3);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .questions ol { padding-left: 1.25rem; }

  .questions li {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text2);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    padding-left: 4px;
  }

  .questions li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .reveal-btn {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text3);
    background: none;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 7px 14px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: inherit;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    width: 100%;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .reveal-btn:hover { background: var(--bg2); border-color: var(--border2); color: var(--text2); }

  .answer-block {
    display: none;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--info-bg);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--info-border);
  }

  .answer-block.shown { display: block; }

  .answer-block p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--info-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .answer-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .answer-block strong { font-weight: 500; }

  .roles-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .role-tag {
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 5px;
    color: var(--text2);
  }

  .role-tag i { font-size: 13px; }

  footer {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text3);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

<header>
  <h1>Cost Analyst — Case Studies</h1>
  <p>Six workplace scenarios for conversation and role-play practice. Read the scenario, discuss the questions, then reveal the suggested resolution.</p>
</header>


<!-- CASE 3 -->
<div class="case case-3">
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="case-num">Case 3</span>
    <div>
      <div class="case-title">Should we drop the "unprofitable" product?</div>
      <div class="case-subtitle">Topic: contribution margin · gross margin · margin analysis</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="case-body">
    <div class="scenario-label">Scenario</div>
    <div class="scenario-text">
      Product Z shows a 4% gross margin — the lowest in the line. Leadership wants to cut it. It sells for $100, variable cost is $60, the company sells 10,000 units a year, and $380,000 in fixed costs is allocated to it from a dedicated production line.
    </div>

    <div class="scenario-label">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-chips">
      <span class="chip">Contribution margin</span>
      <span class="chip">Gross margin</span>
      <span class="chip">Margin analysis</span>
      <span class="chip">Fixed cost</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Roles for role-play</div>
    <div class="roles-row">
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> You — Cost Analyst</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner A — VP of Product</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner B — CFO</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Discussion questions</div>
    <div class="questions">
      <ol>
        <li>Calculate contribution margin per unit and in total.</li>
        <li>If Z is dropped, does the $380,000 disappear?</li>
        <li>What does gross margin hide here that contribution margin reveals?</li>
        <li>VP says "4% speaks for itself" — your response?</li>
        <li>What else would you want to know before recommending?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('shown'); this.innerHTML = this.nextElementSibling.classList.contains('shown') ? '<i class=\'ti ti-eye-off\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Hide suggested resolution' : '<i class=\'ti ti-eye\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Reveal suggested resolution'">
      <i class="ti ti-eye" aria-hidden="true"></i> Reveal suggested resolution
    </button>
    <div class="answer-block">
      <p><strong>Contribution margin = $40/unit × 10,000 = $400,000</strong> — covering the $380,000 fixed cost with room to spare.</p>
      <p>The weak gross margin reflects allocated overhead, not real unprofitability. Unless the dedicated line can be eliminated entirely, dropping Z likely makes things worse, since that overhead would just shift onto other products.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- CASE 4 -->
<div class="case case-4">
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="case-num">Case 4</span>
    <div>
      <div class="case-title">The standard cost nobody updated</div>
      <div class="case-subtitle">Topic: standard cost · price variance</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="case-body">
    <div class="scenario-label">Scenario</div>
    <div class="scenario-text">
      This month's variance report shows an unfavorable price variance: paid $4.80/unit vs. a $4.20 standard. Quantity used was on-budget. The $4.20 standard is 18 months old — the supplier has raised prices twice since.
    </div>

    <div class="scenario-label">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-chips">
      <span class="chip">Standard cost</span>
      <span class="chip">Price variance</span>
      <span class="chip">Cost variance</span>
      <span class="chip">Variance report</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Roles for role-play</div>
    <div class="roles-row">
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> You — Cost Analyst</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner A — Procurement Manager</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner B — Controller</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Discussion questions</div>
    <div class="questions">
      <ol>
        <li>Is this really a performance problem?</li>
        <li>Why do standards go stale?</li>
        <li>How do you explain this without sounding like an excuse?</li>
        <li>Update the standard now, or wait?</li>
        <li>What process prevents this recurring?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('shown'); this.innerHTML = this.nextElementSibling.classList.contains('shown') ? '<i class=\'ti ti-eye-off\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Hide suggested resolution' : '<i class=\'ti ti-eye\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Reveal suggested resolution'">
      <i class="ti ti-eye" aria-hidden="true"></i> Reveal suggested resolution
    </button>
    <div class="answer-block">
      <p>The team is paying market rate — the benchmark is outdated, not their performance. This will keep flagging "unfavorable" every month until the standard is refreshed.</p>
      <p>Recommend a regular review cadence for materials with volatile pricing, so standards don't drift unnoticed again.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- CASE 5 -->
<div class="case case-5">
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="case-num">Case 5</span>
    <div>
      <div class="case-title">Pricing a new product under pressure</div>
      <div class="case-subtitle">Topic: break-even point · CVP analysis · contribution margin</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="case-body">
    <div class="scenario-label">Scenario</div>
    <div class="scenario-text">
      Sales wants to price a new product at $25 to undercut a competitor. Variable cost is $18/unit. New equipment lease: $90,000/year. Maintenance: $10,000 base + $2/unit. Sales projects 12,000 units — admittedly optimistic.
    </div>

    <div class="scenario-label">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-chips">
      <span class="chip">Break-even point</span>
      <span class="chip">CVP analysis</span>
      <span class="chip">Contribution margin</span>
      <span class="chip">Semi-variable cost</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Roles for role-play</div>
    <div class="roles-row">
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> You — Cost Analyst</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner A — Sales Director</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner B — CFO</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Discussion questions</div>
    <div class="questions">
      <ol>
        <li>Split the costs: fixed, variable, semi-variable.</li>
        <li>Calculate contribution margin per unit and break-even units.</li>
        <li>How does break-even compare to the 12,000-unit projection?</li>
        <li>Sales says "make the numbers work" — your response?</li>
        <li>What would you recommend before approving this price?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('shown'); this.innerHTML = this.nextElementSibling.classList.contains('shown') ? '<i class=\'ti ti-eye-off\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Hide suggested resolution' : '<i class=\'ti ti-eye\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Reveal suggested resolution'">
      <i class="ti ti-eye" aria-hidden="true"></i> Reveal suggested resolution
    </button>
    <div class="answer-block">
      <p>Total variable cost = $20/unit ($18 + $2 usage). Fixed costs = $100,000 ($90,000 lease + $10,000 base). Contribution margin = $5/unit → break-even = 20,000 units, well above the 12,000 projected.</p>
      <p>At $25, the product loses money at projected volume. Recommend testing higher price points before committing.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- CASE 6 -->
<div class="case case-6">
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="case-num">Case 6</span>
    <div>
      <div class="case-title">The make-or-buy decision</div>
      <div class="case-subtitle">Topic: relevant cost · contribution margin · fixed cost</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="case-body">
    <div class="scenario-label">Scenario</div>
    <div class="scenario-text">
      A supplier offers to make Component X for $14/unit. In-house cost is $17/unit — but $6 of that is allocated fixed overhead that won't go away if production stops. Operations needs 8,000 units a year.
    </div>

    <div class="scenario-label">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-chips">
      <span class="chip">Relevant cost</span>
      <span class="chip">Contribution margin</span>
      <span class="chip">Fixed cost</span>
      <span class="chip">Cost allocation</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Roles for role-play</div>
    <div class="roles-row">
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> You — Cost Analyst</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner A — Operations Director</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner B — CFO</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Discussion questions</div>
    <div class="questions">
      <ol>
        <li>What's the real in-house cost relevant to this decision — $17 or something else?</li>
        <li>Calculate the per-unit and annual difference between making and buying.</li>
        <li>Operations Director says "$14 is clearly cheaper" — your response?</li>
        <li>What happens to the $6 of fixed overhead if production stops?</li>
        <li>What would change your recommendation?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('shown'); this.innerHTML = this.nextElementSibling.classList.contains('shown') ? '<i class=\'ti ti-eye-off\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Hide suggested resolution' : '<i class=\'ti ti-eye\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Reveal suggested resolution'">
      <i class="ti ti-eye" aria-hidden="true"></i> Reveal suggested resolution
    </button>
    <div class="answer-block">
      <p>The relevant in-house cost is $11/unit ($17 minus the $6 unavoidable overhead) — not $17. Buying at $14 is actually $3/unit <strong>more</strong> expensive once non-avoidable costs are excluded.</p>
      <p>Making in-house is cheaper unless the freed capacity can be used productively elsewhere.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- CASE 7 -->
<div class="case case-7">
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="case-num">Case 7</span>
    <div>
      <div class="case-title">The variance that hid for six months</div>
      <div class="case-subtitle">Topic: cost variance · standard cost · variance report</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="case-body">
    <div class="scenario-label">Scenario</div>
    <div class="scenario-text">
      Year-end review shows labor cost running 12% over standard every month for six months — unflagged because each monthly report showed only dollar amounts, and the figures looked small individually.
    </div>

    <div class="scenario-label">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-chips">
      <span class="chip">Cost variance</span>
      <span class="chip">Standard cost</span>
      <span class="chip">Variance report</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Roles for role-play</div>
    <div class="roles-row">
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> You — Cost Analyst</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner A — Plant Supervisor</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner B — Controller</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Discussion questions</div>
    <div class="questions">
      <ol>
        <li>Why might small monthly variances go unnoticed even when they add up?</li>
        <li>What's missing from a dollar-only variance report?</li>
        <li>How do you raise this without blaming the previous analyst?</li>
        <li>What's your plan to investigate six months of accumulated variance?</li>
        <li>What would you change about how the report is built?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('shown'); this.innerHTML = this.nextElementSibling.classList.contains('shown') ? '<i class=\'ti ti-eye-off\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Hide suggested resolution' : '<i class=\'ti ti-eye\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Reveal suggested resolution'">
      <i class="ti ti-eye" aria-hidden="true"></i> Reveal suggested resolution
    </button>
    <div class="answer-block">
      <p>Dollar-only reports hide trends — a small unfavorable variance each month compounds quietly. Adding percentage-of-standard and a rolling trend would have surfaced this in month two, not month six.</p>
      <p>Frame it as a reporting design gap, not a person's failure, then start by isolating labor hours vs. rate.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- CASE 8 -->
<div class="case case-8">
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="case-num">Case 8</span>
    <div>
      <div class="case-title">The discount that costs more than it saves</div>
      <div class="case-subtitle">Topic: break-even point · contribution margin · CVP analysis</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="case-body">
    <div class="scenario-label">Scenario</div>
    <div class="scenario-text">
      Sales wants to offer a 15% volume discount to a major customer. Current price is $40/unit, variable cost $28/unit. They project order size will rise from 5,000 to 7,500 units.
    </div>

    <div class="scenario-label">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-chips">
      <span class="chip">Contribution margin</span>
      <span class="chip">CVP analysis</span>
      <span class="chip">Break-even point</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Roles for role-play</div>
    <div class="roles-row">
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> You — Cost Analyst</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner A — Sales Director</span>
      <span class="role-tag"><i class="ti ti-user" aria-hidden="true"></i> Partner B — Key Account Manager</span>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label">Discussion questions</div>
    <div class="questions">
      <ol>
        <li>Calculate contribution margin per unit at full price and discounted price.</li>
        <li>Calculate total contribution at 5,000 units (no discount) vs. 7,500 (discounted).</li>
        <li>Is this discount worth it based on the numbers?</li>
        <li>Sales Director says "more volume is always better" — your response?</li>
        <li>What volume would be needed to make the discount break even?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('shown'); this.innerHTML = this.nextElementSibling.classList.contains('shown') ? '<i class=\'ti ti-eye-off\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Hide suggested resolution' : '<i class=\'ti ti-eye\' aria-hidden=\'true\'></i> Reveal suggested resolution'">
      <i class="ti ti-eye" aria-hidden="true"></i> Reveal suggested resolution
    </button>
    <div class="answer-block">
      <p>Discounted price = $34/unit, contribution margin = $6/unit. At 7,500 units: $45,000 total contribution. At full price, 5,000 units × $12 = $60,000.</p>
      <p>The discount reduces total contribution by $15,000 despite higher volume. They'd need about 10,000 units at the discounted price just to match the original $60,000.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<footer>Cost Analyst Case Studies · For classroom conversation practice</footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
